The International Federation of Association Football (FIFA) has congratulated the Tanzania Football Federation (TFF) after the national U-17 Women team, Serengeti Girls qualified for the World Cup in India. The 2022 FIFA Under-17 Women’s World Cup will be played in Bhubaneswar, Goa and Navi Mumbai from October 11 to 30, this year. A statement issued  by TFF Information Officer, Clifford Ndimbo on Thursday said  revealed that the FIFA's director of Competitions, Manolo Zubiria conveyed his congratulatory message through a written letter delivered to the TFF’s General Secretary Kidao Wilfred. During the final stages of the Africa Cup of Nations, the brave Serengeti Girls had beaten Cameroon 5-1 on aggregate thus qualifying for World Cup tournaments for the first time. Other African representatives in the finals which will feature 16 teams are Morocco and Nigeria. Apart from hosts India, other countries qualified for the tournament are China, Japan, Canada, Mexico, the United States, Brazil, Chile, Colombia, New Zealand, France, Germany and Spain.